<2ND_LINE>AM-Bridge Crash, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0469,0368</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two Buses, Vehicle Collide on Bridge</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Leads with 8 grafs to UPDATE with CHP rollback on casuaties,
quotes from students, status of injured; other details; picks up
5th graf: `The accident ...</NOTE>
<DATELINE>HAYWARD, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two tour buses loaded with junior high
school students collided Tuesday night with a vehicle on the San
Mateo Bridge and at least 12 people were injured, two of them
seriously, the highway patrol said.
   Many of the youths were trapped inside the buses for nearly an
hour after the 9 p.m. accident until emergency crews cut openings
through the twisted wreckage. Other students crawled to safety
through smashed windows, Oakland television station KTVU reported.
   ``When we crashed into the other bus everybody started screaming
and crying. The driver swerved but he still hit the bus,'' said
Kristi New, 13, Modesto.
   ``I was sitting up and talking to my friend when I did a total
flip,'' said Callie Stewart, 13, of Modesto. ``Everybody was
screaming. After the bus stopped, people started hugging each other
and asking if they were OK.''
   The injured, some of them adults, were taken to St. Rose and
Eden hospitals in Alameda County, said a California Highway Patrol
dispatcher in San Francisco.
   Two people taken to St. Rose Hospital were listed in stable
condition, and two people, including the bus driver, were listed in
serious condition at Eden Hospital in Castro Valley, according to
hospital spokeswomen.
   About 70 teens were from Loma Linda and Roosevelt junior high
schools in Modesto were aboard the buses, returning from San
Francisco International Airport following a field trip to
Washington, D.C., the highway patrol said.
   The accident occurred in the eastbound lanes about two miles
west of the toll plaza, which is on the Almeda side of the 9.5-mile
bridge linking Almeda and San Mateo counties, said Lt. John Thomas
of the San Mateo bridge district.
   The bridge was closed in both directions following the accident.
   CHP officers at the scene said the buses collided and then
crashed into a center-divider after a passenger car stalled on the
bridge, which is about 20 miles south of San Francisco.
</TEXT>
