<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--CommunistPresident     03-30 0154</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Communist President,0157</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>UMass Students Elect Communist Student Body President</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AMHERST, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 20-year-old journalism major who is a
member of the Young Communist League has been elected student body
president at the University of Massachusetts.
   Certification of the March 15 election comes before the student
senate tonight.
   Jason Rabinowitz of the Bronx, N.Y., was elected president along
with a non-communist co-candidate, Shari Silkof, 20.
   Conservative opponents said the election should not be certified
because of a constitutional prohibition against co-candidacies for
president. But Rabinowitz and Silkoff said they have enough support
to turn back the challenge.
   The winners said they built a coalition of minorities, gays,
lesbians, radicals and women to defeat conservative and moderate
opponents. They said communism was not part of the platform, but
acknowledged that students were aware of Rabinowitz's affiliation.
   Opponents said Rabinowitz was elected because of student apathy
_ about 3,000 of 19,000 students voted.
</TEXT>
