<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--ToddlerCrushed     03-30 0132</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Toddler Crushed,0137</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Toddler Crushed When Mother, 17, Parks Van</HEAD>
<DATELINE>POMPANO BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 1{-year-old boy was fatally crushed
when his mother accidentally ran him over as she was parking a van,
authorities said.
   ``It was an accident,'' Joelie Borja, 17, said tearfully. ``I
just ran over him. He was running after a toy, and I didn't see him
come outside.''
   Pablo Sanchez died an hour after he stepped in front the van.
   ``This happens because people leave the doors open, and kids
just run in and out at will,'' said Mike Marker, a traffic homicide
investigator with Pompano Beach police.
   The car was traveling about 5 mph when the toddler ran
underneath the passenger side of the van, police said.
   No charges have been filed in the case.
</TEXT>
