<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Iran-Quake     03-30 0119</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Iran-Quake,0124</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Earthquake Shakes Southwest Iran</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An earthquake shook southwest Iran early
today and initial reports indicated there were casualties and
damage.
   Iran's official Islamic Republic News Agency said relief teams
were dispatched to Dehdasht, 340 miles from Tehran in the Boyer
Ahmed province, to ``help the victims and estimate the damage.'' It
did not give a casualty figure.
   Dehdasht has a population of 105,000.
   It said the geophysics center in Tehran registered the epicenter
near Dehdasht.
   The quake measured 5.2 on the Richter scale.
   An earthquake of 5 can cause considerable damage. A 7 reading is
a ``major'' earthquake, capable of widespread heavy damage; 8 is a
``great'' quake, capable of tremendous damage.
</TEXT>
