<1ST_LINE>r a PM-People-Suzy     03-30 0381</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-People-Suzy,0397</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Suzy's Revenge! Gossip War Is On!</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Suzy says ... Revson's a rat.
   But _ why should WE care?
   Well, that's entertainment in the world of New York gossip.
   New York Post columnist Suzy, it seems, is just a little, eentsy
bit miffed over a column by her upstart rival in New York Newsday,
James Revson.
   Revson wrote last week that he was ``a bit heartbroken'' to find
that _ HORRORS _ Suzy had written about a posh party at the
Metropolitan Museum without attending it.
   Specifically, Revson wrote, ``Suzy ticked off the names of 32
well-known people who, she wrote, had attended the party. ... Well,
there's a sad truth here. Not one of those boldfaced folks showed
up at the museum. NONE. ZERO. ZILCH.''
   Suzy (who actually has two real names, Aileen Mehle) wasn't
pleased.
   Yes, Suzy admitted in today's column, she used a press release
to write about the party in advance so she could slip away for ``a
little vacation on the beautiful, windswept isle of Mustique in the
Caribbean. It was heaven.''
   And yes, she said, it's true that some of the people she said
were at the party never showed up, even though they were listed in
the press release.
   And yes, she said, ``I should have yanked the whole thing or at
least the names the release said would attend.''
   But is Suzy contrite? Not on your life.
   ``I bow in accuracy and meticulousness and decency to no one,''
she wrote. ``That is the reason I have survived as a star all these
long years _ that and because in my field I am the best and the
brightest there is.
   ``And dear readers, fans and publicity-seekers, I would like to
go on record as telling the world that any place ... Revson is, I
will not be. Do not invite me anywhere if you invite him. Just call
it a boycott _ or even a Suzycott.''
   Revson's column made such a splash that even the august Times
took notice, printing a story AND A PICTURE of Revson.
   Not only did Revson show himself to be a rat, Suzy said today,
he gave himself away as ``malicious, sneaky, ugly-mean.''
   Got it?
   More in this space tomorrow. We hope.
</TEXT>
