<HEAD>Nigerian Cargo Plane Slides Off Runway</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COPENHAGEN, Denmark (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Nigerian plane coming to collect a
cargo of cows overshot the runway after landing at a Danish
airfield, police said Wednesday.
   One person was injured and the DC-8 was badly damaged when it
slid about 100 yards off the runway in the town of Billund on
Tuesday, said acting police commissioner Bjarne Jensen said.
   The plane, carrying eight crew members, was to transport cattle
to Egypt, he said. The cause of the accident was not known.
