the president Wednesday.
   Brady, 36, will succeed Jay Stephens in the position. Brady has
been deputy assistant to Vice President George Bush since 1985.
Before that he was in the Justice Department.
   He was deputy attorney general of California in 1978 and 1979.
   The president also announced the appointment of William J.
Landers, 36, now with the Justice Department, as associate counsel
