<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--CBS Schedule,0185</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>CBS Comedy Experiment Fails; Cagney & Lacey Back to Monday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   CBS is dropping its low-rated Tuesday lineup of
comedies and putting ``Cagney & Lacey'' back in its Monday night
time period.
   CBS is facing a third-place finish in the prime-time ratings
this season for the first time ever and was trying to add more
half-hour comedies to its drama-heavy schedule.
   The critically acclaimed ``Frank's Place'' was spared the ax
Tuesday night and will be returned to the schedule shortly, CBS
said. It had been moved from Monday to Tuesday in the schedule
shakeup earlier this month. ``Cagney & Lacey'' will replace
``Wiseguy'' on Monday, but ``Wiseguy'' also will return soon, CBS
said.
   ``Trial and Error,'' ``Coming of Age'' and ``My Sister Sam''
have had their last Tuesday broadcasts, and CBS announced no plans
to bring them back. Those comedies, plus ``Frank's Place'' were the
four lowest-rated network shows in last week's Nielsens.
   CBS will replace the Tuesday lineup with theatrical movies in
the meantime, and the detective series ``Houston Knights'' will
return April 26.
