<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Haring,0121</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Former Outlaw Artist Goes Legit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Once Keith Haring was an outlaw, an artist who
repeatedly was ticketed by police for drawing white chalk stick
figures on black poster advertising boards in subway stations.
   But on Tuesday he was back in the subway, this time with the
blessing of the Transit Authority, which is placing on subway cars
and in stations 5,000 Haring-designed posters that urge young
people to read.
   ``FILL YOUR HEAD WITH FUN! START READING!'' say the posters,
which feature a drawing of a kid's head filled with amusing,
Haringesque creatures.
   ``This is great,'' Haring said as he autographed copies of the
poster in a station. ``It's come full circle.''
</TEXT>
