   Tabatha Foster, a Kentucky toddler who's the
longest survivor of a five-organ transplant, is moving up on
hospital charts in her battle to survive.
   Doctors at Children's Hospital of Pittsburgh upgraded her
condition to fair on Tuesday. The 3-year-old Madisonville, Ky.,
girl received a new liver, pancreas, small intestine and parts of a
stomach and colon on Nov. 1. She had suffered from a congenital
defect known as short gut syndrome.
