<HEAD>Major Cocaine Shipment Found on Ecuadorean Ship</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PANAMA CITY, Panama (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Government agents confiscated nearly
685 pounds of cocaine aboard an Ecuadorean boat traveling through
the Panama Canal, a pro-government newspaper reported Wednesday.
   The report in Critica said agents of the National Department of
Investigations detained the ship Isla Baltra after receiving
information from Ecuadorean police about the cargo.
   The boat was headed for Barcelona, Spain.
   Critica said the ship was stopped as it completed its transit of
the canal, boarded by navy squads and special anti-narcotics
agents, then taken to the port of Balboa where it was searched.
   The illegal drug was found in 278 packages in a container of
prefabricrated building material aboard the ship, the report said.
It did not say if any arrests were made or give the estimated value
of the drug.
   The United States has called for the ouster of Panama's
strongman, Gen. Manuel Noriega, since he was indicted on
drug-trafficking charges in February in Florida. He says he is
innocent.
