<HEAD>Democrats Offering Political Plums For Corporate Donations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Democrats are soliciting corporate donations to
help pay for their national convention in Atlanta this summer, and
they're offering some political plums in return.
   A four-color brochure sent out this week to 600 corporations in
Georgia and the Southeast offers tickets to the convention, choice
hotel rooms, transportation and exclusive parties to those willing
to chip in.
   ``This convention provides a unique opportunity for corporations
to get their message across to governors, members of Congress,
foreign ambassadors,'' says Nancy Parrish, a fund-raising
consultant who helped design the convention sales package.
   A $15,000 contributor would get two convention tickets, access
to a hospitality suite, rooms at area hotels and seats on VIP buses
running between hotels and the convention site.
   For $200,000, a contributor will receive floor seats or a
skybox, a private reception room, more hotel rooms, exclusive
parties and limousine service.
