<HEAD>Big Drug Hauls By British Customs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Customs authorities said they seized 198 pounds of
Colombian cocaine with a street value of about $22 million
Wednesday and arrested two men.
   A Customs and Excise spokesman, who under British practice
refused to be identified, said it was the second largest haul of
cocaine in Britain.
   Earlier, Customs said it seized two tons of marijuana, worth
about $5.6 million, at Tilbury docks in east London from a
container ship that came from Port Harcourt, Nigeria.
   Six men and a woman were charged Wednesday with smuggling the
marijuana, which Customs said was hidden in a cargo of compressed
rubber bales. Initial discoveries of the cache were made more than
two weeks ago.
   Customs agents from London's Heathrow Airport made the cocaine
haul but officials refused to give details except to say the two
arrests were in Surrey, a county neighboring London.
   Last November, Customs found 457 pounds of cocaine worth about
$90 million in a container on a ship at Southampton.
