with aggravated assault, simple assault, burglary and robbery. ``I
believe he was identified by a witness in the house,'' Witte said.
   Meanwhile, Arnold Goode continued to refuse to cooperate in the
investigation of his shooting March 22, Witte said.
   After the shooting, Goode checked into the
Presbyterian-University of Pennsylvania Medical Center with a
gunshot wound to his left hand but left abruptly before the
consultation ended.
   The mayor has acknowledged that both men are his nephews but has
refused further comment.
