<HEAD>Popular Panda Pop Put Under Observation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pe-Pe, the father of Mexico's beloved panda
family, was put under medical observation after two tumors were
found, the director of the Chapultepec Zoo said Wednesday.
   ``It is a matter of two inflamed tumors, but we have just about
discounted the idea that it could be cancer,'' Maria Elena Hoyo
said.
   China gave Pe-Pe and his mate, Ying-Ying, to Mexico in September
1975. They have four surviving offspring by natural conception, the
largest such panda family outside of China.
   Ms. Hoyo said a general examination is planned April 11 or 12 to
determine what caused the tumors.
   She said the 13-year-old panda weighs 249 pounds, down from his
usual 275 to 285 pounds. Pandas have a life expectancy of about 20
years.
