moved broadly higher Tuesday as the Dow Jones average of 30
industrial stocks climbed 18.57 to 1,998.34.
   The dollar moved higher in foreign exchange trading and gold
prices rose.
   Bond prices rebounded, and interest rates backed off two-month
highs.
   Platinum prices surged, but energy prices, grain and soybeans
finished mixed.
