<2ND_LINE>BC-EEC-Inflation ,0126</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>EEC Prices Up 0.3 Percent in February</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Consumer prices in the 12-nation
European Economic Community rose 0.3 percent in February from
January and 3 percent from the year-earlier month, the EEC reported.
   The Common Market's 3 percent year-on-year inflation rate in
February remained unchanged from January, Eurostat, the EEC
statistical office, said Wednesday. That compares with inflation
rates of 0.9 percent in Japan and 3.9 percent in the United States.
   The 0.3 percent February rate continues the trend of moderate
price increases established at the beginning of 1987, Eurostat said.
   It said inflation was modest in all EEC countries except
Portugal and Denmark, which recorded monthly increases of 1.4
percent and 0.8 percent, respectively.
</TEXT>
