<2ND_LINE>PM-Night Trading,0160</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Philadelphia Exchange Adds British Pounds, Swiss Francs to Night
Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Philadelphia Stock Exchange is expanding
its night session trading list with the addition of futures and
options on the British pound and the Swiss franc.
   The exchange announced Tuesday it will open trading in the new
currencies, April 14.
   Night trading at the stock exchange began Sept. 16 with
transactions in American and European-style options on Australian
dollars, Deutsche marks and Japanese yen. It averages about 5,000
contracts a night.
   Futures in all five currencies also will be offered by the
Philadelphia Board of Trade, a subsidiary of the exchange.
   The night trading session, which runs from 7 p.m. to 11 p.m. EST
Sunday through Thursday. The daytime session runs Monday through
Friday from 8 a.m. to 2:30 p.m.
   Options are traded on the night currencies plus Canadian
dollars, French francs and European currency units.
