<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Texaco     03-30 0192</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Texaco,0199</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Texaco Files Backup Supreme Court Appeal Just in Case</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Texaco Inc. said it filed an appeal of a
multibillion-dollar damage judgment to the U.S. Supreme Court on
Wednesday, but stressed the move was only a formality in the event
its settlement with Pennzoil Co. fell through.
   Texaco agreed in December to pay Pennzoil $3 billion in return
for Pennzoil dropping the $10.3 billion judgment. The settlement
was the keystone of a bankruptcy reorganization plan that was
approved by a U.S. Bankruptcy Court judge in White Plains, N.Y.,
last week.
   The plan is scheduled to take effect April 7, at which time
Texaco is to transfer $3 billion to Pennzoil and begin payment of
$2.6 billion to its other creditors. Texaco said it would withdraw
its request for a Supreme Court hearing at that time.
   Pennzoil won the judgment when a Houston jury ruled Texaco had
improperly interfered with a Pennzoil acquisition of part of Getty
Oil Co. and bought all of Getty itself.
   Texaco filed for bankruptcy court protection last April to avoid
having to pay a $11 billion security bond while appealing that
judgment.
</TEXT>
