<DOCNO> AP880330-0319 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-03-30-88 2105EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-TurnerBroadcasting     03-30 0214</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Turner Broadcasting,0222</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Posts Losses of $27.2 Million In 4th-Qtr, $131.2 Million For Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Turner Broadcasting System Inc. said Wednesday
its fourth-quarter loss narrowed to $27.2 million in 1987 from
$65.9 million a year earlier as its revenue rose 23.9 percent.
   The broadcasting and sports company said revenue for the quarter
ended Dec. 31 rose to $193.1 million from $155.9 million a year
earlier.
   Operating income for the quarter more than doubled to $64.9
million from $27.4 million for the same quarter the previous year.
   The company said fourth quarter earnings included a charge of
$13.1 million to reduce the value of certain internally produced
programming to its estimated net realizable value. The earnings
also included a $10 million credit resulting from recognition of
copyright fee income which had been the subject of litigation.
   For the year ended Dec. 31, the company lost $131.2 million on
revenue of $652.4 million, compared to a net loss of $187.3 million
on revenue of $556.9 million for 1986.
   Operating income for the year climbed 69 percent to $217.4
million from $128.4 million a year earlier.
   TBS owns Cable News Network and CNN Headline News, SuperStation
TBS, the Atlanta Braves professional baseball team and a majority
ownership in the Atlanta Hawks professional basketball team.
</TEXT>
