<FILEID>AP-NR-03-30-88 2300EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f AM-HarcourtBrace     03-30 0150</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Harcourt Brace,0155</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Board Names a President; Jovanovich Continues as Chief Executive</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The board of directors of Harcourt Brace
Jovanovich Inc. on Wednesday elected Ralph D. Caulo as president
and chief operating officer and retained longtime HBJ boss William
Jovanovich as chairman and chief executive.
   Caulo, 53, had been one of several executive vice presidents who
constituted the office of president of the company, which has major
interests in publishing, theme parks and insurance.
   Caulo's new post indicates he will take over more of the
day-to-day operations, but officials of the Orlando-based company
either were unavailable or would not comment on a brief statement
issued after the directors' meeting. Caulo will continue to oversee
HBJ's textbook publishing and related operations, according to the
statement.
   Jovanovich, 68, has run the company since 1955 and there were no
indications that he was relinquishing any of his control.
</TEXT>
